	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 27.8.4. C. Laetorius succeeded Q. Mucius Scaevola." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1529> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1529" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Imperium prorogued in Sardinia (Liv. 25.3.6; cf. 26.1.11)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1494> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1494" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Imperium prorogued in Sardinia (Liv. 24.44.5)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1456> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1456" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Imperium prorogued in Sardinia (Liv. 24.10.4, and 112)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1415> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1415" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Went to Sardinia but fell ill and had to be temporarily relieved of command (Liv. 23.34.10-17, cf. 41.1-42.7). See Promagistrates, on Manlius." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1412> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1412" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/3> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Election Liv. 23.24.4 Provinces Liv. 23.30.18." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1278> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1278" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Chr. 354 (Levino et Scevola). Livy (29.11.3; 30.23.5) states that Valerius Laevinus was twice Consul. We must suppose with Degrassi 118, and 119, on 210) that Valerius and Mucius were faultily elected, and either abdicated or never entered upon their magistracy. See Degrassi 118, 442f.; Münzer, Gent. Val. 45, no. 34 on Valerius." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1277> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1277" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/4> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "In 65 B.C. also the Chr. 354 keeps the names of Sulla and Paetus, who were elected but did not take office. Degrassi would assume that Scevola in Chr. 354 refers to a member of the Mucian Gens, and favors the Praetor of 215. Praetorships after consulships were still not infrequent, and became necessary under the stress of the Hannibalic war." .
